[10] New Zealand
Date: Tue 20 Nov 2018
Source: Stuff [extracted, edited]
https://www.stuff.co.nz/the-press/news/108744082/Milford-Sound-woman-tests-positive-for-measles


A 30-year-old Southland woman has been struck with measles.

The woman, a resident of Milford Sound, tested positive for the highly-contagious and potentially deadly virus on Tue 20 Nov 2018. She did not require hospital treatment.

It is the 1st confirmed case of measles in New Zealand since May 2018.

Southern medical officer of health Dr Susan Jack said it was not known whether the woman was immunised against measles.

Three people were confirmed to have measles in Christchurch and Otago.

Public Health South was working to identify all of the woman's close contacts to determine their immunisation status and offer vaccination.

Earlier this year [2018], there was a measles outbreak across the South Island. Five people, including a baby, contracted the virus. Two were hospitalised.

[Byline: Jo McKenzie-McLean]

